\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {10.1}{\ignorespaces Sex-stratified analysis of treatment outcomes across all intervention strategies. \textbf  {Top left:} Survival rates show consistent female advantage across all treatments, with combination therapy achieving the highest success rates in both sexes. \textbf  {Top right:} Median survival times mirror the survival rate patterns, with females consistently living longer than males regardless of treatment. \textbf  {Bottom left:} Treatment benefit over control reveals that while both sexes benefit from therapy, males show larger absolute improvements with combination treatment. \textbf  {Bottom right:} Distribution analysis shows that while average outcomes favor females, there's substantial individual variation—some male patients achieve excellent outcomes while some female patients don't respond to treatment.}}{50}{figure.caption.42}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:sex_stratified_results}{{10.1}{50}{Sex-stratified analysis of treatment outcomes across all intervention strategies. \textbf {Top left:} Survival rates show consistent female advantage across all treatments, with combination therapy achieving the highest success rates in both sexes. \textbf {Top right:} Median survival times mirror the survival rate patterns, with females consistently living longer than males regardless of treatment. \textbf {Bottom left:} Treatment benefit over control reveals that while both sexes benefit from therapy, males show larger absolute improvements with combination treatment. \textbf {Bottom right:} Distribution analysis shows that while average outcomes favor females, there's substantial individual variation—some male patients achieve excellent outcomes while some female patients don't respond to treatment}{figure.caption.42}{}}
